Reasoning: The paper deals with wireless communication systems and relaying protocols, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of buffer-aided relaying also falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of successive interference cancellation (SIC), which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
